The course deals with concept and scope of labour law; conclusion, amendment and termination of employment contract; working and rest time and holidays; remuneration; health and safety at the workplace; the rights and duties of the parties to the employment contract; collective labour relations and resolution of labour disputes.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide understanding about labour law regulation and practice in Estonia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completing the course, a student: *knows the legal regulation of labour relations in Estonia and its connections with the EU labour law; *knows problems arising when implementing labour law acts and possibilities to solve them; *is able to resolve labour disputes.
